{"questionId":"30730413","questionHtml":"<p>State whether the events <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>I</mi></math> are mutually exclusive. Justify your answer.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>∩</mo><mi>I</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>≠</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>OR&nbsp; </strong>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>∩</mo><mi>I</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>≠</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note: </strong>Accept <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mi>T</mi></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mi>I</mi></mfenced><mo>≠</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>∪</mo><mi>I</mi></mrow></mfenced></math> provided probabilities are shown.</p>\n<p>Accept an equivalent statement in words such as “some (<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>13</mn></math>) students went to both cafes” or “students could go to both cafes”. Condone <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>and</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>I</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>≠</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>OR&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>T</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>and</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>I</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>≠</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>no, they are not mutually exclusive&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Do not award <em><strong>R0A1</strong></em>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"30730413","referenceCode":"24M.1.SL.TZ1.2e","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"State whether the events T and I are mutually exclusive. Justify your answer.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"e","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.5—Probability concepts, expected numbers","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.6—Combined, mutually exclusive, conditional, independence, prob diagrams"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}